# Core contract (Rust crates)

Each `crates/extralife-<device>` implements `extralife_core::Device` and only
that. The trait is the whole seam — see `crates/extralife-core/src/lib.rs`.

## Rules

- **Deterministic.** Same ROM + same inputs ⇒ byte-identical framebuffer, every
  run. No wall-clock, no time-seeded RNG, no threads in the hot path.
- **Headless.** No screen, audio device, or event loop assumed. The harness
  drives `step_frame` and reads `framebuffer()`.
- **Plain data at the edge.** `framebuffer()` is always RGBA8888, row-major,
  length `screen().framebuffer_len()`. The WASM/JS boundary is a memory read.
- **`load_rom` fully resets.** Two loads = two clean runs.
- **`load_state` is atomic.** On `Err`, leave the core unchanged.
- **`save_state`/`load_state` round-trip** on the same core version.

## Layout per crate — same skeleton for every device

The edges where cores touch the rest of the system are fixed, so every core
looks the same from outside. The *internals* are yours: split CPU/PPU/APU/mapper
into as many modules as the hardware needs. Mandatory files and names:

```
crates/extralife-<device>/
  Cargo.toml            # extralife-core.workspace = true; wasm-bindgen dep;
                        # [lib] crate-type = ["cdylib", "rlib"];
                        # image as a dev-dependency for golden tests only
  src/lib.rs            # pub struct <Device> + `impl Device`; `mod wasm;`
                        # plus device internals (own modules: cpu.rs, ppu.rs, …)
  src/wasm.rs           # #[wasm_bindgen] `Core` class — the SAME method surface
                        # as every other core (see extralife-chip8/src/wasm.rs):
                        # new, width/height getters, loadRom, stepFrame,
                        # setButton(usize,bool), framebuffer()->Vec<u8>
  src/tests.rs          # `#[cfg(test)] mod tests;` — precise unit tests for
                        # opcodes/quirks + the Device contract round-trip check
  tests/golden.rs       # golden-image regression: run test ROMs N frames,
                        # diff framebuffer vs tests/golden/<device>/*.png;
                        # UPDATE_GOLDEN=1 regenerates
```

Then wire it up (unchanged pattern):
- Test ROMs: git submodule under `tests/roms/`, never copied in.
- Golden PNGs: committed under `tests/golden/<device>/`, human-verified once.
- Smoke harness: one `DeviceEntry` in `packages/smoke-harness/src/devices.ts`
  + a Vite alias (see the `browser-smoke-test` skill).

Keep `extralife-core` tiny. Adding a trait method touches every core — do it
only when a real device forces it, and give it a sane default so silent cores
(no audio yet) compile unchanged.
